        "title": "feat: add code-mode MCP API files",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add virtual `API.list()` / `API.read()` declaration files for code-mode MCP namespaces (`mcp/index.d.ts`, `mcp/<server>.d.ts`)\n- expose MCP calls through `MCP.<server>.<tool>()` in code mode while keeping MCP tools hidden from the model-visible tool list\n- preserve plugin metadata across provider tool-schema normalization so MCP tools stay classified after OpenAI Responses normalization\n- add deterministic and live Docker gateway smokes that make an agent read the API files, call a file-backed MCP fixture, and prove no `$api()` / `tools.search` pollution\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/runtime-plan/tools.test.ts src/agents/code-mode.test.ts test/scripts/docker-e2e-plan.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-tool-construction-plan.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `bash -n scripts/e2e/mcp-code-mode-gateway-docker.sh scripts/e2e/mcp-code-mode-gateway-live-docker.sh && node --check scripts/e2e/mock-openai-server.mjs`\n- `pnpm test:docker:mcp-code-mode-gateway`\n- `pnpm test:docker:live-mcp-code-mode-gateway`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --prompt 'Review only the MCP code-mode/API-file/docker-e2e/runtime-plan changes. Ignore unrelated pre-existing dirty packages/*/dist files in this checkout. The prior finding about exec/wait allowlists was addressed by removing the MCP allowlist bypass; confirm no remaining actionable issues.'`\n",
